cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the throughput and delay performance of wireless relay networks, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new relay scheme for point-to-point communication systems, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of relay networks and proposes a new relay scheme, which can be considered as a control problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of relay buffers to exploit time diversity, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia communication systems. 
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper proposes a relay scheme that utilizes multiple relays, which can be considered as a multi-agent system.
